settings.title: What makes Beast Health™ different?
settings.content: The Beast® Blender was designed and engineered for optimal blending performance for fresh, natural ingredients in order to help you more easily achieve a healthy lifestyle, and become your strongest on the inside. Between our innovative 12-Rib vessel design optimized for increased turbulence and blending efficiency, and our leak-resistant, ultra-durable Tritan™ vessels, we’ve got you covered. And yes, it can make a damn good frozen margarita and grind coffee beans too. Head over to the Design & Tech section of our website to learn more.

settings.title: What are the terms of the 2-year limited warranty?
settings.content: Lucky for you, we have a whole page dedicated to this very question.

settings.title: Do I need to register for my warranty?
settings.content: Yes, registering for your warranty is required. It helps us communicate important information regarding your product and serve you with warranty service.

settings.title: What do I need to do to register my warranty?
settings.content: All you have to do is visit our Warranty Registration page to fill out your registration form. You will need your product’s model number and serial number, date of purchase, and purchase location.

settings.title: Where are my model and serial numbers located?
settings.content: They’re both located on the bottom of the unit. The model number is located under the Beast® logo and the serial number is located on the white sticker under the barcode.

settings.title: What’s the return policy?
settings.content: We truly believe you’ll love all of your Beast Health™ products, but if for some reason you’re not completely satisfied with your order, we will offer you a full refund excluding the return shipping cost, as long as you contact us and ship the return back to us within 30 days of the initial delivery. You, the customer, are responsible for all return shipping costs associated with your order. Reach out below!

settings.title: What's the shipping policy?
settings.content:
Orders can ship up to 2-5 business days after placing your order. Priority and Expedited Shipping applies to orders placed before 10am PT; orders placed after that time will be shipped the following business day.

Your payment method will be charged upon order placement. Charges are based on the total weight of packaged products shipped to each address. All shipping charges include handling, order processing, item selection, packaging, and transportation of items. Additional shipping charges may apply to some items due to location or large size. Price estimates are shown in the cart and final cost per weight range is determined based on shipping address during checkout.

settings.title: Where can I find Beast® products?
settings.content: We are currently selling exclusively online, so you’ve come to the right place! Check out our products here.

settings.title: Which countries do you sell in?
settings.content: We are selling in the United States for now, with more countries coming soon.

settings.title: Will I be charged sales tax?
settings.content: Orders that ship to the following states will have sales tax applied: Alabama, Arizona, Arkansas, California, Colorado, Connecticut, Washington, D.C., Florida, Georgia, Hawaii, Idaho, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Kentucky, Louisiana, Maine, Massachusetts, Maryland, Michigan, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri, North Carolina, North Dakota, New Jersey, New Mexico, New York, Nebraska, Nevada, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, South Carolina, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Virginia, Vermont, West Virginia, Washington, Wisconsin, Wyoming.

settings.title: How do I care for my Beast Health™ products?
settings.content:
Blender Base

• Clean periodically with damp towel

Blade Assembly

• Rinse under tap water to clean, using a soapy sponge if necessary

All other Components

• Dishwasher Safe - Top Rack Only

settings.title: Are Blending Vessels microwave safe?
settings.content: Beast Health™ Vessels and accessories are not intended to be used in the microwave, which may result in damage to the accessories.

settings.title: What are Beast Health™ Blending Vessels made of? Are they BPA free?
settings.content: Our ultra-durable Blending Vessels are made of BPA-free Tritan™, and have thick walls to provide a leak-proof seal with the Blade Assembly.

settings.title: What are the blades made of?
settings.content: Grade 301 Stainless Steel. For the perfect balance of durability and corrosion resistance. Like six mini samurai swords spinning at 18,000 RPM.

settings.title: Are all components of the B10 and Hydration System dishwasher safe?
settings.content: Blending Vessels and accessories can be washed on the top rack of the dishwasher only. DO NOT wash the Blade Assembly or Blender Base in the dishwasher. All components of the Hydration System can be washed on the top rack of the dishwasher only.

settings.title: What do the different color lights mean on the front of the unit?
settings.content:
• Amber - Solid: unit on, no blade assembly and/or blending vessel connected

• White - Solid: unit on, ready to blend

• Green - Solid: unit on, blending in progress

• Amber - Flashing: motor overload

• Red - Flashing: vessel contents too hot to safely blend

settings.title: Why isn’t my blender turning on?
settings.content: We promise no judgment, but: Is the blender plugged in? Did you turn the orange power switch on (located at the back of the Blender Base)?

settings.title: Why isn’t my blender blending?
settings.content: Is the Blade Assembly and/or Blending Vessel properly connected? Confirm that the Blade Assembly is firmly threaded onto the Blending Vessel. Then confirm that the Blade Assembly and Blending Vessel are twisted onto the base until it clicks into place and the LED indicator displays a Solid-White color light.

settings.title: Why does my blender sound like that (that meaning laboring)?
settings.content: Your Blending Vessel may be overfilled, or Blending Vessel contents may be stuck. If your Blending Vessel is overfilled, try taking some ingredients out of your Vessel. If contents are stuck, try adding more liquid and/or giving it a good shake (not while attached to the Blender Base).

settings.title: What should I use the large 1000mL Vessel vs. the small 500mL Vessel for?
settings.content: As they say, the world is your oyster, but we like to use the 1000mL Vessel for Nutrition Blends, Dessert Blends, and Hydration Blends™ , and the 500mL Vessel for salsas, hummus, nut butters, etc. If you need some inspiration, check out our recipes here.

settings.title: How do I assemble the Beast Blender?
settings.content: Why, we’re glad you asked. Check out our quick start video.

settings.title: In what order should I fill my Blending Vessel?
settings.content:
Add your preferred ingredients to the vessel in the following order for the best results:

• Liquids

• Ice

• Produce

• Leafy greens

• Powders, seeds, nuts, nut butters, honey

For more information, check out your “B10 Getting Started + The Perfect Blend Card” found in your User Manual that came with your shipped unit.

settings.title: What is the maximum capacity of the Beast Blender?
settings.content: When blending, the big Vessel has a maximum fill volume of 700 mL. If you have the small Vessel (included in the B10+), that has a maximum fill volume of 350 mL.

settings.title: How do I pulse ingredients?
settings.content: To pulse, press the standby switch on the front of the blender for less than 1 second. Repeat until you achieve your desired texture. And while we’re at it, a quick note: pulsing is a useful way to coarsely chop ingredients without totally emulsifying them. This method is particularly useful for chopping your infusion ingredients, grinding coffee beans, making chunky salsa, chopping onions, and adding chunks of ingredients to an already smooth mixture for texture.

settings.title: How do I make my blend extra smooth and creamy?
settings.content: We’re not overexaggerating here -- we really created the best blender technology could offer so all you have to do is kick back, relax, and enjoy the Beast Blender show. BUT here’s an insider tip: approximately ⅓ of your ingredients should be liquid to ensure a smooth blend.

settings.title: Why is my protein powder sticking to the bottom of the Vessel?
settings.content: We suggest adding fine or sticky ingredients last, to prevent them from getting stuck to the bottom of the Vessel.

settings.title: How should I store my Beast Blender?
settings.content: Straight up. On the counter.

settings.title: Can I blend hot ingredients, particularly liquids, in my Beast Blender?
settings.content: NEVER BLEND HOT INGREDIENTS. Doing so may cause excessive steam and pressure to build up in the Vessel, resulting in the potential risk of the Vessel and Blender Base separating and thereby possibly resulting in personal injury and/or property damage. If the Beast® Blender overheats, a thermal switch will activate and shut off the motor.

settings.title: Can I blend carbonated ingredients or rising agents in the B10 Health Blender?
settings.content: NEVER BLEND CARBONATED INGREDIENTS OR RISING AGENTS IN THE BEAST® BLENDER. These ingredients incorporate air bubbles that produce foam and cause breads and cakes to rise. Blending these ingredients may cause excessive pressure buildup in the container and may cause personal injury to the user or property damage. Common leavening agents such as baking powder, baking soda, cream of tartar, cultured or fermented ingredients, egg whites, salt of hartshorn, whey protein, sesa moss, and yeast should not be blended in the Beast® Blender.

settings.title: Can I blend and/or pulse frozen ingredients in the Blender?
settings.content: Absolutely. In fact, we encourage it to make your blend extra delicious. If you need any recipes including frozen ingredients, click here for some of our favorites.

settings.title: Can I ground coffee in the Blender?
settings.content: Why yes, you can. In our opinion, ground coffee is made best through pulsing. To pulse, press the standby button on the front of the blender for less than 1 second. Step and repeat.

settings.title: What ingredients should not be blended inside the Beast Blender?
settings.content: Hot ingredients, carbonated ingredients, and rising agents. For more information, see relevant questions above.

settings.title: Why are my ingredients not blending well?
settings.content:
Have you tried filling your Vessel in the order suggested? For reference, add your preferred ingredients to the Vessel in the following order for the best results:

• Liquids

• Ice

• Produce

• Leafy greens

• Powders, seeds, nuts, nut butters, honey

For more information, check out your “B10 Getting Started + The Perfect Blend Card” found in your User Manual that came with your shipped unit.

settings.content: Our Why Blend page has some recipes and ingredient information to help you get started.

settings.content: Pure glass.

settings.content: We’ve got just the thing for you. Click here for our quick start video to get you started.

settings.title: I’m having trouble attaching the Chamber Mount to the Drinking Lid. Any suggestions?
settings.content: We’ve found that dunking the Chamber Mount in water, or running it under some water, helps attach it much more smoothly.

settings.title: How can I get the infused water to be colorful?
settings.content: We’ve found that when you pulse your infusion ingredients first, and then drop them into your Infusion Chamber, the water in your Hydration Vessel takes on a beautiful color. To see this in action, check out our quick start video.

Strengthen Immunity
settings.text: Nutrition and immunity go hand in hand, and we’re here to give you the tools to put that power… well, in your hands. Each blend lets you pack in more produce—think vitamins, antioxidants, fiber, and all that goodness—than you’d get from eating alone. The result? Stronger immunity, more energy, and greater health.

settings.title: Hydrate Better
settings.text: Depending on who you ask, hydrating isn’t exactly fun—which is why we created sleek (dare we say sexy?) vessels to up your hydration. Whether you’re mixing up new blends (full of water-rich produce) or making your own H20 infusions, you’re giving your body what it needs. Consider the Beast Blender + Hydration System your go-to hydration stations to amp up the flavor, whether at home or on the go.

settings.title: We’re not selling magic, but we can make spinach disappear…
settings.text: One of the best parts of blending is that certain ingredients just disappear into the blend with other (read: tastier) ingredients.

settings.title: The beauty of blending is making it your own.
settings.text: Whether you have specific flavors or wellness goals in mind, you can mix and match ingredients to your heart’s (and health’s) content. Secret bonus? All ingredients here have nutrients that support immunity.

settings.title: Nutrition Blends
settings.desc: Our take on a traditional smoothie—just with more fruits & vegetables optimized with nutrients that boost our immune systems.

settings.title: Hydration Blends™
settings.desc: Think ‘spa water’ on steroids. Our Hydration Blends™ are less dense than Nutrition Blends, yet still packed full of nutrients, and keep you hydrated throughout the day.

settings.title: Dessert Blends
settings.desc: Craving a cherry on top? Look no further than our Dessert Blends, which are our version of a more classic dessert.

settings.title: Infusions
settings.desc:
Our best-in-class technology gives you the power to infuse—literally—more nutrients into your water, taking your hydration to the next level in your Beast® Hydration System.

By quickly pulsing your ingredients before infusing, your infusion will have tons of flavor and far more nutrients compared to infusing large chunks of ingredients.

settings.title: Beast Health™ recipes
settings.text: To help get you started with blending, we specially crafted the recipes below with a focus on building your immunity and making you Strong Inside™.

settings.title: Whatever you blend, blend it in a Beast.
The Beast Blender
settings.text:
Best-in-class blending performance.

Thoughtfully designed, front-to-back.

settings.title: Silky Smooth Blends
settings.text: Innovative 12-Rib vessel design for increased turbulence and blending efficiency.

settings.title: A Blade with a Brain
settings.text:
The Beast Blender monitors its blade speed, and makes constant adjustments to maintain consistent speed and torque.

It also monitors internal temperature to avoid overheating and blending of hot liquids.

settings.title: Leak-Resistant Seal
settings.text: Ultra-durable, super thick Tritan™  vessels provide a leak-resistant seal with the blade assembly. No spills here.

settings.title: Safe & Intelligent
settings.text: Our industry-leading electronic interlock system confirms that the vessel, blade assembly, and blender base are all securely connected before it will begin blending.

settings.title: Meticulously Designed
settings.text: We considered how each component could be improved to increase longevity and reduce vibrations and noise—that’s why our blade assembly mounts precisely to the base like a lens to a camera body.

settings.title: Is 'overbuilt' a good word?
